.Write a MongoDB query to create and drop database. 
 
Query: > show dbs > use mydb 
 
 
> db.mycol.insert({"name":"ABC"}) 
 
 
> show dbs 
 
 
> db.dropDatabase() > show dbs 
 

 B.Write a MongoDB query to create,display and drop collection. 
 
Query: 
 
> show dbs > use mydb 
 
 
> db.createCollection("mycol",{capped:true,autoIndexId:true,size:6142810,max:10000} ) 
 
 
> db.mycol.insertOne({item:"canvas",qty:100,tags:["cotton"],size:{h:28,w:35.5,uom:"c m"}}) 
 
 
> db.mycol.find() 
 
 
 
 
> db.mycol.find().pretty() 
 
 
> db.mycol.drop() > db.mycol.find() 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

 C.Write a MongoDB query to insert, query, update and delete a document. 
 
Query: 
 
> db.mycol.insert([{title:"MongoDB Tutorial",description:"MongoDB is no sql database",by:"Tutorials Point",tags:["mongodb","database","NoSQL"],likes:100}]) 
 
 
> db.mycol.find().pretty() 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
> db.mycol.update({title:"MongoDB Tutorial"},{$set:{title:"MongoDB Overview"}}) 
 
 
> db.mycol.find().pretty() 
 
 
> db.mycol.remove({title:"MongoDB Overview"}) > db.mycol.find().pretty()
